{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error CS0254\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0254\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0254\"\nms.assetid: 85b2ab1e-0011-4f1d-9181-76b9c9f3d914\n---\n# Compiler Error CS0254\nThe right hand side of a fixed statement assignment may not be a cast expression  \n  \n The right side of a [fixed](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/fixed-statement.md) expression may not use a cast. For more information, see [Unsafe Code and Pointers](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md).  \n  \n The following sample generates CS0254:  \n  \n```csharp  \n// CS0254.cs  \n// compile with: /unsafe  \nclass Point  \n{  \n   public uint x, y;  \n}  \n  \nclass FixedTest  \n{  \n   unsafe static void SquarePtrParam (int* p)  \n   {  \n      *p *= *p;  \n   }  \n  \n   unsafe public static void Main()  \n   {  \n      Point pt = new Point();  \n      pt.x = 5;  \n      pt.y = 6;  \n  \n      fixed (int* p = (int*)&pt.x)   // CS0254  \n      // try the following line instead  \n      // fixed (uint* p = &pt.x)  \n      {  \n         SquarePtrParam ((int*)p);  \n      }  \n   }  \n}  \n```\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,165],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Compiler Error CS0254\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"CS0254\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"CS0254\"\nms.assetid: 85b2ab1e-0011-4f1d-9181-76b9c9f3d914","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0254","nodes":[{"pos":[0,21],"content":"Compiler Error CS0254","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0254","pos":[0,21]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[172,193],"content":"Compiler Error CS0254","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0254","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0254","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"The right hand side of a fixed statement assignment may not be a cast expression","pos":[194,274]},{"content":"The right side of a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>fixed<ept id=\"p1\">](../../csharp/language-reference/keywords/fixed-statement.md)<